verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto Aaron and to his sons, that they separate themselves from the holy things of the children of Israel, and that they profane not my holy name in those things which they hallow unto me: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 2Speak unto Aaron and to his sons, that they separate themselves from the holy things of the children of Israel, and that they profane not my holy name in those things which they hallow unto me: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Say unto them, Whosoever he be of all your seed among your generations, that goeth unto the holy things, which the children of Israel hallow unto the Lord, having his uncleanness upon him, that soul shall be cut off from my presence: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 3Say unto them, Whosoever he be of all your seed among your generations, that goeth unto the holy things, which the children of Israel hallow unto the Lord, having his uncleanness upon him, that soul shall be cut off from my presence: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: What man soever of the seed of Aaron is a leper, or hath a running issue; he shall not eat of the holy things, until he be clean. And whoso toucheth any thing that is unclean by the dead, or a man whose seed goeth from him;
verses.verse_html:
4What man soever of the seed of Aaron is a leper, or hath a running issue; he shall not eat of the holy things, until he be clean. And whoso toucheth any thing that is unclean by the dead, or a man whose seed goeth from him; ▼
▼ running…: Heb. running of the reins

footnotes.body_text: ▼ running…: Heb. running of the reins
footnotes.body_html: ▼ running…: Heb. running of the reins

verses.text_plain: Or whosoever toucheth any creeping thing, whereby he may be made unclean, or a man of whom he may take uncleanness, whatsoever uncleanness he hath;
verses.verse_html: 5Or whosoever toucheth any creeping thing, whereby he may be made unclean, or a man of whom he may take uncleanness, whatsoever uncleanness he hath;

tokens.text: whereby he may be made unclean
of whom he may take uncleanness

verses.text_plain: The soul which hath touched any such shall be unclean until even, and shall not eat of the holy things, unless he wash his flesh with water.
verses.verse_html: 6The soul which hath touched any such shall be unclean until even, and shall not eat of the holy things, unless he wash his flesh with water.

verses.text_plain: And when the sun is down, he shall be clean, and shall afterward eat of the holy things; because it is his food.
verses.verse_html: 7And when the sun is down, he shall be clean, and shall afterward eat of the holy things; because it is his food.

verses.text_plain: That which dieth of itself, or is torn with beasts, he shall not eat to defile himself therewith: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 8That which dieth of itself, or is torn with beasts, he shall not eat to defile himself therewith: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: They shall therefore keep mine ordinance, lest they bear sin for it, and die therefore, if they profane it: I the Lord do sanctify them.
verses.verse_html: 9They shall therefore keep mine ordinance, lest they bear sin for it, and die therefore, if they profane it: I the Lord do sanctify them.

verses.text_plain: There shall no stranger eat of the holy thing: a sojourner of the priest, or an hired servant, shall not eat of the holy thing.
verses.verse_html: 10There shall no stranger eat of the holy thing: a sojourner of the priest, or an hired servant, shall not eat of the holy thing.

verses.text_plain: But if the priest buy any soul with his money, he shall eat of it, and he that is born in his house: they shall eat of his meat.
verses.verse_html:
11But if the priest buy any soul with his money, he shall eat of it, and he that is born in his house: they shall eat of his meat. ▼
▼ with…: Heb. with the purchase of his money

tokens.text: of it, and he that is born

footnotes.body_text: ▼ with…: Heb. with the purchase of his money
footnotes.body_html: ▼ with…: Heb. with the purchase of his money

verses.text_plain: If the priest’s daughter also be married unto a stranger, she may not eat of an offering of the holy things.
verses.verse_html:
12If the priest’s daughter also be married unto a stranger, she may not eat of an offering of the holy things. ▼
▼ a stranger: Heb. a man a stranger

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a stranger: Heb. a man a stranger
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a stranger: Heb. a man a stranger

verses.text_plain: But if the priest’s daughter be a widow, or divorced, and have no child, and is returned unto her father’s house, as in her youth, she shall eat of her father’s meat: but there shall no stranger eat thereof.
verses.verse_html: 13But if the priest’s daughter be a widow, or divorced, and have no child, and is returned unto her father’s house, as in her youth, she shall eat of her father’s meat: but there shall no stranger eat thereof.

verses.text_plain: And if a man eat of the holy thing unwittingly, then he shall put the fifth part thereof unto it, and shall give it unto the priest with the holy thing.
verses.verse_html: 14And if a man eat of the holy thing unwittingly, then he shall put the fifth part thereof unto it, and shall give it unto the priest with the holy thing.

tokens.text: thereof unto it, and shall give

verses.text_plain: And they shall not profane the holy things of the children of Israel, which they offer unto the Lord;
verses.verse_html: 15And they shall not profane the holy things of the children of Israel, which they offer unto the Lord;

verses.text_plain: Or suffer them to bear the iniquity of trespass, when they eat their holy things: for I the Lord do sanctify them.
verses.verse_html:
16Or suffer them to bear the iniquity of trespass, when they eat their holy things: for I the Lord do sanctify them. ▼
▼ suffer…: or, lade themselves with the iniquity of trespass in their eating

footnotes.body_text: ▼ suffer…: or, lade themselves with the iniquity of trespass in their eating
footnotes.body_html: ▼ suffer…: or, lade themselves with the iniquity of trespass in their eating

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 17And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto Aaron, and to his sons, and unto all the children of Israel, and say unto them, Whatsoever he be of the house of Israel, or of the strangers in Israel, that will offer his oblation for all his vows, and for all his freewill offerings, which they will offer unto the Lord for a burnt offering;
verses.verse_html: 18Speak unto Aaron, and to his sons, and unto all the children of Israel, and say unto them, Whatsoever he be of the house of Israel, or of the strangers in Israel, that will offer his oblation for all his vows, and for all his freewill offerings, which they will offer unto the Lord for a burnt offering;

tokens.text: and for all his freewill offerings

verses.text_plain: Ye shall offer at your own will a male without blemish, of the beeves, of the sheep, or of the goats.
verses.verse_html: 19Ye shall offer at your own will a male without blemish, of the beeves, of the sheep, or of the goats.

verses.text_plain: But whatsoever hath a blemish, that shall ye not offer: for it shall not be acceptable for you.
verses.verse_html: 20But whatsoever hath a blemish, that shall ye not offer: for it shall not be acceptable for you.

tokens.text: for it shall not be acceptable

verses.text_plain: And whosoever offereth a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the Lord to accomplish his vow, or a freewill offering in beeves or sheep, it shall be perfect to be accepted; there shall be no blemish therein.
verses.verse_html:
21And whosoever offereth a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the Lord to accomplish his vow, or a freewill offering in beeves or sheep, it shall be perfect to be accepted; there shall be no blemish therein. ▼
▼ sheep: or, goats

verses.text_plain: Blind, or broken, or maimed, or having a wen, or scurvy, or scabbed, ye shall not offer these unto the Lord, nor make an offering by fire of them upon the altar unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 22Blind, or broken, or maimed, or having a wen, or scurvy, or scabbed, ye shall not offer these unto the Lord, nor make an offering by fire of them upon the altar unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Either a bullock or a lamb that hath any thing superfluous or lacking in his parts, that mayest thou offer for a freewill offering; but for a vow it shall not be accepted.
verses.verse_html:
23Either a bullock or a lamb that hath any thing superfluous or lacking in his parts, that mayest thou offer for a freewill offering; but for a vow it shall not be accepted. ▼
▼ lamb: or, kid

verses.text_plain: Ye shall not offer unto the Lord that which is bruised, or crushed, or broken, or cut; neither shall ye make any offering thereof in your land.
verses.verse_html: 24Ye shall not offer unto the Lord that which is bruised, or crushed, or broken, or cut; neither shall ye make any offering thereof in your land.

verses.text_plain: Neither from a stranger’s hand shall ye offer the bread of your God of any of these; because their corruption is in them, and blemishes be in them: they shall not be accepted for you.
verses.verse_html: 25Neither from a stranger’s hand shall ye offer the bread of your God of any of these; because their corruption is in them, and blemishes be in them: they shall not be accepted for you.

tokens.text: of any of these; because their corruption
in them: they shall not be accepted

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 26And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: When a bullock, or a sheep, or a goat, is brought forth, then it shall be seven days under the dam; and from the eighth day and thenceforth it shall be accepted for an offering made by fire unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 27When a bullock, or a sheep, or a goat, is brought forth, then it shall be seven days under the dam; and from the eighth day and thenceforth it shall be accepted for an offering made by fire unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And whether it be cow or ewe, ye shall not kill it and her young both in one day.
verses.verse_html:
28And whether it be cow or ewe, ye shall not kill it and her young both in one day. ▼
▼ ewe: or, she goat

footnotes.body_html: ▼ ewe: or, she goat

verses.text_plain: And when ye will offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving unto the Lord, offer it at your own will.
verses.verse_html: 29And when ye will offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving unto the Lord, offer it at your own will.

verses.text_plain: On the same day it shall be eaten up; ye shall leave none of it until the morrow: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 30On the same day it shall be eaten up; ye shall leave none of it until the morrow: I am the Lord.

tokens.text: none of it until the morrow

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall ye keep my commandments, and do them: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 31Therefore shall ye keep my commandments, and do them: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Neither shall ye profane my holy name; but I will be hallowed among the children of Israel: I am the Lord which hallow you,
verses.verse_html: 32Neither shall ye profane my holy name; but I will be hallowed among the children of Israel: I am the Lord which hallow you,

verses.text_plain: That brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 33That brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the Lord.
